<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-454-909  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 454 909.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 28 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for IBM: user interface simplifies DOS commands. (DimestoreSoftware's DOS User Interface) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Dimestore Software (product introduction).andO;Product:   MS-DOS (Operating system) (computer programs)DOS User Interface (Operating system enhancement) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionUser InterfaceUtility Programs.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR IBM: User Interface Simplifies DOS Commands MISSION VIEJO,CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1990 AUG 28 (NB) -- Dimestore Software (Mission Viejo,Calif.) is offering DOS User Interface (DUI), which performs frequently usedDOS commands without the usual command line entries associated with DOS.andP;  Italso adds features not found in the DOS environment, the company says.andM;Features include the ability to view up to 72 file names in one window;visual display of an entire disk's directory structure; the ability to viewfiles as text or &quot;hexdump&quot; format; and full smooth scrolling and positioningin file View.andM;According to the company, DUI has the &quot;easiest to learn and use&quot; userinterface of any DOS shell on the market.andP;  Main commands are constantlyvisible and activated by single keystrokes, or by point and shoot menuselection.andP;  DUI makes it easier to traverse directories, the company says,with five methods to change directories, most of which are single keystrokeactivations.andM;DUI comes with a 45-page manual and requires an IBM PC/XT/AT or compatible,DOS 2.0 or higher and 256 kilobytes of memory.andP;  It lists for $24.95 and isavailable from Dimestore Software, 22731 Via Tercero, Mission Viejo, CA92691.andP;  714/454-1550.andM;(Computer Currents/19900808)</TEXT></DOC>